                    <msContents>
                        <summary>
                            <seg type="para">This fragment is a single folio from an Evangelion, containing
                                one of the few known copies of <title>Marcus Mamunas' Symbolon paraphrase</title>. 
                                Little is known about this individual, who probably lived between the 15th and 16th centuries (PLP no. 16574). 
                                The text was found by I. Sakkelion in Cos in a 15th-century manuscript, now lost. 
                                The other witnesses to the text are two 16th-century manuscripts in Mount Athos
                                (<bibl subtype="external" type="MS">
                           <ref target="https://archive.org/details/cataloguegreekm01lampgoog/page/n184/mode/2up">
                                    Hagion Oros, Mone Iberon 535 (4655 Lambros)</ref>
                        </bibl>, 
                                <bibl subtype="external" type="MS">
                           <ref target="http://www.pipm.gr/sites/default/files/eustratiadis_lavras.pdf">
                                    Hagion Oros, Mone Megistes Lauras Ω 130 (1942 Eustratiades )</ref>
                        </bibl>).
                                The text of the Symbolon or Creed, in 30 verses of 16 syllables, does not take into account the principles 
                                laid down by the Union of Churches of the Council of Ferrara-Florence (1438-45).</seg> 
                            <seg type="para">The fragment was acquired by Constantin von Tischendorf 
                                and bought from his heirs by Cambridge University Library in 1876.</seg>
                            <seg type="para">Dr Matteo Di Franco</seg>
                        </summary>

                        <textLang mainLang="grc">Greek</textLang>

                        <msItem n="1">
